a rather hit-n-miss group of noir short stories (richmond noir, salt lake city noir, spokane noir, oklahoma city noir, etc [a joke, please]) books has finally come home to it's hard hitting roots (
 , 
 ) with a new collection highlighting speed, meth, go fast, hillbilly dentistry, whatever you might call it. editor joseph mattson has brought together a great and diverse group of writers to tell us stories about speed old and new. it;s a fast read too, one can buzz through it in just a few moments. hah. all are winners, from Scott Phillips signature style of matter-of-fact revenge, to megan abbott's stylish justifications for drugs as help-metes(sp?) to mattson's own vibrating scores and just WHERE? will one draw the line in fuckedupedness. cold and frosty stories to warm your noir needs.
